DOC.HEADLINE: JC WOMEN ' S BASKETBALL ; HARBOR WINS STATE CROWN
DOC.TEXT: The Los Angeles Harbor College women ' s basketball_team defeated Golden West , 83-70 , at Solano College in Suisun City to win the state community_college championship . Harbor ' s JoAnn Williams scored 36 points and teammate LaTasha Burnett , named the state tournament ' s most_valuable_player , had 28 points and 10 rebounds . The two sophomore guards are both from Lynwood High . Harbor , located in Wilmington , finished 31-6 and earned its first women ' s state title in any sport . Michelle Kravik scored 14 points to lead Golden West of Huntington Beach ( 33-5 ) .
